As a result of the argument that "those who [need] get what they need," while those who do not need it argue that it is "[unequal]," [equality] is achieved by not giving things to those who need them as well, since there is no point in giving things to those who do not need them.

I heard a story about a restaurant that complained that "free refills" at restaurants were unfair and that "free refills" were no longer offered.
